```sql
   CREATE TABLE Authors (
      login text primary key,
      email text,
      first_name text,
      last_name text
   )

   CREATE TABLE Books (
      id integer primary key autoincrement,
      title text,
      author text references authors(login),
      language text,
      created date
  )

  CREATE TABLE Categories (
     category text,
     book integer references books(id),
     unique (book, category)
  )
```

---

**List.Categories:** List the book categories in the database in reverse alphabetical order.  
% answer = '''
SELECT DISTINCT category
  FROM Categories
  ORDER BY category DESC
'''
{{!sql(answer, dbs=dbs, points=25, name='List.Categories')}}
% include('viewAnswer')

---

**List.Book.And.Categories:** List all the book titles in alphabetical order along with their categories.  
For example, if the book titled <i>Plurals: Canes, nomine Montius et Daisia</i>
had categories <b>Animals and Nature</b> and <b>Fairy and Folk Tales</b> this
would be displayed on two lines.
% answer = '''
SELECT title, category
  FROM Books B, Categories C
  WHERE b.id=c.book
  ORDER BY title ASC
'''
{{!sql(answer, dbs=dbs, sort=1, points=25, name='List.Book.And.Catories')}}
% include('viewAnswer')

---

**List.First.Book.Per.Category:** List the book categories in alphabetical order along with
the first book id (the one with the smallest id) that used that category.  
% answer = '''
SELECT category, min(book) as book_id
  FROM Categories
  GROUP BY category
  OrDER BY  book_id
'''
{{!sql(answer, dbs=dbs, points=25, name='List.First.Book.Per.Category')}}
% include('viewAnswer')

